Others: The Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Houston Rockets with a score of 126-107.
Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Chet Holmgren combined for 58 points in the game.
Jalen Williams and Isaiah Joe added 14 points each, while Ajay Mitchell had 12 points and 7 assists off the bench.
The Thunder's defense remained strong, maintaining the top spot in the NBA defensive rating ladder with a 97.3 rating.
The Thunder's upcoming schedule includes tougher opponents such as the Golden State Warriors and the Phoenix Suns.
